 water and power stations,<ref>[http://www.syriahr.com/2016/11/21/\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a-\u0633\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0627-\u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0645\u0642\u0631\u0627\u0637\u064a\u0629-\u062a\u062d\u0631\u0632-\u062a\u0642\u062f\u0645\u0627\u064b-\u062c\u062f/ \u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0633\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0645\u0642\u0631\u0627\u0637\u064a\u0629 \u062a\u062d\u0631\u0632 \u062a\u0642\u062f\u0645\u0627\u064b \u062c\u062f\u064a\u062f\u0627\u064b \u0648\u062a\u0631\u0641\u0639 \u0625\u0644\u0649 48 \u0639\u062f\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0631\u0649 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0632\u0627\u0631\u0639 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u064a\u0637\u0631 \u0639\u0644\u064a\u0647\u0627]</ref><ref name=Hawar110/> Tabqa Airbase,<ref name=\"Tabqa airbase\" /><ref name=Bloomairbase>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-03-26/syrian-opposition-calls-on-us-to-spare-civilians-in-raqqa|title=US-backed Forces Capture Syrian Air Base From IS|first=Philip|last=Issa|work=The Associated Press|publisher=Bloomberg L.P.|date=26 March 2017|accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref> [[Al-Thawrah|Tabqa city]], [[Tabqa Dam]], and [[Baath Dam]]<ref name=ArabiyaTabqa/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN1862E4|title=U.S.-backed Syria militias say Tabqa, dam captured from Islamic State|first=Ellen|last=Francis|date=10 May 2017|publisher=Reuters}}</ref><ref name=baath>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-raqqa-idUSKBN18V0EX|title=U.S.-backed Syrian forces seize dam west of Raqqa from Islamic State: SDF|work=Reuters|date=4 June 2017}}</ref>\n* The SDF comes within 5 km of the Islamic State's capital city of Raqqa, in early February 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/video-kurdish-led-forces-5km-isis-capital-raqqa-rapid-offensive/|title=Video: Kurdish-led forces only 5km from the ISIS capital of Raqqa after rapid offensive|first=Paul|last=Antonopoulos|date=10 February 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n* The SDF enters [[Battle of Raqqa (2017)|Raqqa city]] on 6 June 2017, and completely captures it on 17 October 2017\n|combatant1  = {{flagicon image|Flag of Syrian Democratic Forces.svg}} '''[[Syrian Democratic Forces]]'''<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Rojava.svg}} [[Self-Defense Forces (Rojava cantons)|Self Defence Forces]] (HXP)<ref name=\"HXP\">{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/self-defense-fighters-join-wrath-of-euphrates/|title=Self-defense fighters join Wrath of Euphrates|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|author=J.O|date=5 February 2017|access-date=5 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170206104142/http://en.hawarnews.com/self-defense-fighters-join-wrath-of-euphrates/|archive-date=6 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><br />{{flagicon image|Red and Black Mutualist Flag.png}}{{flagicon image|International Freedom Battalion original banner.svg}} [[Left-wing politics|Leftist]]/[[Anarchism|anarchist]] volunteers{{efn|name=Left|Most leftist foreign volunteers fight as part of the YPG,{{sfnp|Harp|2017|pp=43-49}} though some have also formed independent units, such as the [[Antifascist International Tabur]]{{sfnp|Harp|2017|p=49}} and the [[International Revolutionary People's Guerrilla Forces|IRPGF]], or joined the [[International Freedom Battalion]]. The latter is a larger unit, mostly composed of Kurdish and Turkish communists.<ref name=\"IFB\">{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/kurdistan/raqqa-s-fall-will-bring-the-end-of-erdogan|title='Raqqa's fall will bring the end of Erdo\u011fan'|first=Sinan|last=Deniz|work=ANF News|date=13 November 2016|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref>}}<br />\n{{flagicon image|Seal of Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve.svg|border=no}} '''[[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve|CJTF\u2013OIR]]'''\n* {{flag|United States}}\n* {{flag|France}}<ref name=\"gains\">{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/kurdish-arab-forces-syria-gains-raqqa-province/3646230.html|