ath of Euphrates reveals outcomes|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=14 November 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114131224/http://en.hawarnews.com/550-km2-liberated-wrath-of-euphrates-reveals-outcomes/|archivedate=14 November 2016}}</ref><br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Syrian Democratic Forces.svg}}{{flagicon|Syrian opposition}} Fayad Ghanim<br />{{small|([[Raqqa Hawks Brigade]] commander)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/a-military-commander-we-will-besiege-gangs-on-all-sides/|title=A military commander \"we will besiege gangs on all sides\"|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=7 November 2016|access-date=7 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170512154509/http://en.hawarnews.com/a-military-commander-we-will-besiege-gangs-on-all-sides/|url-status=dead|archive-date=2017-05-12}}</ref><br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Syrian Democratic Forces.svg}}{{Flagicon image|Flag of Liwa Thuwar al-Raqqa.svg}} Abu Issa<br />{{small|([[Jabhat Thuwar al-Raqqa]] chief commander)}}<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Syrian Democratic Forces.svg}}{{flagicon|Syrian opposition}} Muhedi Jayila<br />{{small|([[Syria's Tomorrow Movement#Military wing|Elite Forces]] commander)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/02/arab-fighters-join-kurdish-led-sdf-fight-raqqa-2/|title=More Arab fighters join Kurdish-led SDF in fight for Raqqa|work=[[ARA News]]|first=Heysem|last=Haci|date=5 February 2017}}</ref><br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Syrian Democratic Forces.svg}}{{flagicon image|Flag of al-Sanadid Forces.svg}} Bandar al-Humaydi<br />{{small|([[Al-Sanadid Forces]] military chief commander)}}<ref name=\"reveals\" /><br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Rojava.svg}} Siyamend Welat<br />{{small|(HXP chief commander)}}<ref name=\"campaign successfully\">{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-campaign-successfully-advances-98-villages-hamlets-liberated/|title=Wrath of Euphrates: campaign successfully advances, 98 villages, hamlets liberated|publisher=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=12 February 2017|accessdate=12 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170213164123/http://en.hawarnews.com/wrath-of-euphrates-campaign-successfully-advances-98-villages-hamlets-liberated/|archive-date=13 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><br />{{flagicon|USA}} Lt. Gen. [[Stephen J. Townsend]]<br />{{small|(CJTF\u2013OIR chief commander)}}<br />''For other anti-ISIL commanders, see [[Order of battle for the Raqqa campaign (2016\u201317)|order of battle]]''\n|commander2  = {{flagicon|Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|size=23px}} [[Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi]]{{WIA}}<br />{{small|(Leader of ISIL)}}<ref name=\"al-Baghdadi movements\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/12/29/politics/baghdadi-movements-us-aware-isis/index.html|title=US aware of recent Baghdadi movements|first=Barbara Starr, CNN Pentagon|last=Correspondent|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"Baghdadi WIA\">{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/02/iraqi-airstrikes-hit-isis-leaders-al-baghdadis-fate-unknown/|title=Iraqi airstrikes hit ISIS leaders, al-Baghdadi's fate unknown|work=[[ARA News]]|author=|date=14 February 2017}}</ref><br />{{flagdeco|Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant}} [[Abu Jandal al-Kuwaiti]]{{KIA}}<br />{{small|(Leading ISIL commander for Raqqa defenses, c. 11\u201326 December)}}<ref name=\"al-Kuwaiti\">{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2016/12/isis-commander-raqqa-killed-us-airstrike/|title=ISIS commander of Raqqa killed in US airstrike|publisher=[[ARA News]]|first=Sadredin|last=Kino|date=27 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"al-Kuwaiti2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idINKBN14G0NW |title= U.S.-backed force in Syria advances towards IS-held dam|publisher=Reuters|date=27 December 2016|accessdate=27 December 2016}}</ref><br />{{flagdeco|Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant}} Abu Saraqeb al-Maghribi<br />{{small|(Head of security in [[Al-Thawrah]])}}<ref name=\"officials\">{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/20