oungsters who joined terror outfit ISIS are based in Raqqa: Report|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"3 maps\">{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/the-battle-of-raqqa-with-isis-will-drag-on-with-high-costs-2017-3|title=3 maps that show why it won't be easy defeating ISIS|publisher=}}</ref> {{small|(estimate by Western SDF volunteers & some experts)}}\n* Raqqa city: c. 5,000 fighters<ref name=\"key supply\">{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/islamic-state-access-key-supply-routes-despite-losing-ground/3696437.html|title=Islamic State Losing Ground, Still Using Key Supply Routes|first=Jeff|last=Seldin|work=[[Voice of America]]|date=27 January 2017}}</ref>\n* Large number of reinforcements from [[Mosul]] and [[al-Bab]]<ref name=\"key supply\" />\n** 200 Iraqi reinforcements<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=55557|title=In the first response from the leadership to \"the Military Amir of Raqqa\", about 200 Syrian fighters arrive from Iraq to Raqqa|work=SOHR|date=25 November 2016}}</ref>\n* Unknown number of [[Military use of children|child soldiers]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-liberated-children-exploited-by-isis/|title=SDF fighters liberated children exploited by ISIS|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|date=18 January 2017|access-date=19 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170809123500/http://en.hawarnews.com/sdf-fighters-liberated-children-exploited-by-isis/|archive-date=9 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/video-kurdish-led-forces-capture-isis-child-soldiers-near-raqqa/|title=Video: Kurdish-led forces capture ISIS child soldiers near Raqqa|work=[[al-Masdar News]]|first=Paul|last=Antonopoulos|date=18 January 2017}}</ref>\nUnknown number of [[Unmanned aerial vehicle|UAVs]] (drones)<ref name=\"drone\">{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/strong-clashes-in-makmen-and-khanez-fronts/|title=Strong clashes in Makmen and Khanez fronts|work=[[Hawar News Age