tle of Raqqa (2017)}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n|conflict    = Raqqa campaign (2016\u201317)\n|width       = 350px\n|partof      = the [[Syrian Kurdish\u2013Islamist conflict (2013\u2013present)]] and the [[American-led intervention in the Syrian Civil War|American-led intervention]] in the [[Syrian Civil War]] \n|image       = [[File:Northern Raqqa Offensive (November 2016).svg|350px]][[File:Battle of Raqqa (2017).svg|350px]]\n|caption     = '''Top: '''A map of the SDF advances in the [[Raqqa Governorate]];<br />'''Bottom: '''A map of the SDF advances inside of [[Raqqa]] city itself\n|date        = 6 November 2016 \u2013 20 October 2017<br />({{Age in months, weeks and days|year1=2016|month1=11|day1=06|year2=2017|month2=10|day2=20}})<ref name=2017balance>{{cite web|url=https://www.ypgrojava.org/2017-Balance-Sheet-of-War-%E2%80%93-Syrian-Democratic-Forces|title=2017 Balance Sheet of War \u2013 Syrian Democratic Forces|date=3 January 2018|publisher=}}</ref>\n|place       = [[Raqqa Governorate]] and northern [[Deir ez-Zor Governorate]], [[Syria]]\n|coordinates = {{Coord|35.9500|N|39.0167|E|source:wikidata_type:event_region:SY-RA|display=inline,title}}\n|territory   = The [[Syrian Democratic Forces|SDF]] captures more than {{convert|7400|km\u00b2}} of territory from [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] during the first, second and third phases of the campaign<ref name=defense20170315>{{cite web|url=https://www.defense.gov/News/Transcripts/Transcript-View/Article/1119873/department-of-defense-press-briefing-by-col-dorrian-via-teleconference-from-bag/ |title=Department of Defense Press Briefing by Col. Dorrian via teleconference from Baghdad, Iraq |date=15 March 2017 |publisher=U.S. Department of Defense}}</ref>\n|result      = Decisive SDF / CJTF-OIR victory\n* The SDF captures more than 236 villages, hamlets and strategic hills, two water and power stations,<ref>[http://www.syriahr.com/2016/11/21/\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a-\u0633\u0648\u0631\u064a\u0627-\u06