017\n|combatant1  = {{flagicon image|Flag of Syrian Democratic Forces.svg}} '''[[Syrian Democratic Forces]]'''<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Rojava.svg}} [[Self-Defense Forces (Rojava cantons)|Self Defence Forces]] (HXP)<ref name=\"HXP\">{{cite web|url=http://en.hawarnews.com/self-defense-fighters-join-wrath-of-euphrates/|title=Self-defense fighters join Wrath of Euphrates|work=[[Hawar News Agency]]|author=J.O|date=5 February 2017|access-date=5 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170206104142/http://en.hawarnews.com/self-defense-fighters-join-wrath-of-euphrates/|archive-date=6 February 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><br />{{flagicon image|Red and Black Mutualist Flag.png}}{{flagicon image|International Freedom Battalion original banner.svg}} [[Left-wing politics|Leftist]]/[[Anarchism|anarchist]] volunteers{{efn|name=Left|Most leftist foreign volunteers fight as part of the YPG,{{sfnp|Harp|2017|pp=43-49}} though some have also formed independent units, such as the [[Antifascist International Tabur]]{{sfnp|Harp|2017|p=49}} and the [[International Revolutionary People's Guerrilla Forces|IRPGF]], or joined the [[International Freedom Battalion]]. The latter is a larger unit, mostly composed of Kurdish and Turkish communists.<ref name=\"IFB\">{{cite web|url=https://anfenglish.com/kurdistan/raqqa-s-fall-will-bring-the-end-of-erdogan|title='Raqqa's fall will bring the end of Erdo\u011fan'|first=Sinan|last=Deniz|work=ANF News|date=13 November 2016|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref>}}<br />\n{{flagicon image|Seal of Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve.svg|border=no}} '''[[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve|CJTF\u2013OIR]]'''\n* {{flag|United States}}\n* {{flag|France}}<ref name=\"gains\">{{cite web|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/kurdish-arab-forces-syria-gains-raqqa-province/3646230.html|title=Kurdish-Arab Forces in Syria Make Gains in Raqqa Province|work=[[Voice of America]]|first=Sirwan|last=Kajjo|date=21 December 2016}}</ref>\n* {{flag|United Kingdom}}<ref name=\"GB\">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/12/25/operation-raqqa-british-raf-pilots-switch-bombing-raids-heart/|title=Operation Raqqa: British RAF pilots to switch bombing raids to 'the heart' of Isil|publisher=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|first=Steven|last=Swinford|date=25 December 2016|accessdate=16 January 2017|newspaper=The Telegraph}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Germany}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tagesschau.de/ausland/luftangriffe-syrien-aufklaerungsbilder-bundeswehr-101.html|title=Zivile Opfer in Syrien. Bundeswehr in verheerenden Luftschlag involviert|work=[[Tagesschau (Germany)]]|author1=Volkmar Kabisch|author2=Reiko Pinkert|language=German|date=29 March 2017|accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref>\n{{flag|Iraqi Kurdistan}}<ref name=\"Peshmerga in Raqqa offensive\" />\n----\n'''[[Southern Raqqa offensive (June 2017)|Co-belligerents]]:'''<br />{{flagicon image|Flag_of_Syria.svg}} [[Syria|Syrian Arab Republic]]<ref name=\"Reuters\">{{cite web | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-syria-army-idUSKBN1941QO | title=Syrian army advances west of Raqqa: Hezbollah military media unit | publisher=Reuters | date=13 June 2017 | accessdate=13 June 2017}}</ref><br />{{flag|Russia}}<ref name=\"Russia\">{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/02/russia-bombs-isis-positions-in-raqqa/|title=Russia bombs ISIS positions in Raqqa|first=Hozan|last=Mamo|publisher=[[ARA News]]|date=18 February 2017|accessdate=18 February 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219004345/http://aranews.net/2017/02/russia-bombs-isis-positions-in-raqqa/|archivedate=19 February 2017}}</ref>\n|combatant2  = '''{{flag|Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant}}'''\n|commander1  = {{flagicon image|Flag of Syrian Democratic Forces.svg}}{{flagicon image|People's Protection Units Flag.svg|border=no}} Sipan Hemo<br />{{small|(YPG chief commander)}}<ref name=\"hemo\">{{cite web|url=http://aranews.net/2017/03/kurdish-ypg-